ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
SAVE IT: How easy can water rationing be (B1)? Sometimes, quite easy, says the 
Metropolitan Water District of Southern California. 
It says the No. 1 residential waste is water for lawns that ends up on 
sidewalks and driveways. Indoors, leaky toilets are the biggest sinners. Fixing 
toilets and adjusting sprinkler heads may be all it takes to conserve. Lily Eng 
and Jan Herman 
